To-Do List

Description
A responsive web application for managing daily tasks with a sleek interface and local persistence. Users can add, mark as complete, and delete tasks, with the option to switch between light and dark themes. Perfect for organizing your day efficiently!
Technologies Used

React 19: Library for building reusable UI components (note: using experimental 19.1.1 in this project).
Tailwind CSS: Framework for fast and responsive styling.
Vite: Lightweight build tool and development server.
TypeScript: Adds static typing for robust code.
ESLint: Linting tool to maintain code quality and consistency.

How to Run the Project Locally
Follow these steps to run the project on your local machine:

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/react-todo-app.git

(Replace your-username/react-todo-app with your actual repository URL.)

Navigate to the project directory:
cd react-todo-app


Install dependencies:
npm install


Start the development server:
npm run dev


Open in your browser:

Visit the URL provided in the terminal (typically http://localhost:5173) and start using your To-Do List!



Features

Add new tasks.
Mark tasks as completed.
Delete tasks.
Filter tasks (all, completed, pending).
Switch between light and dark themes.
Responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop.
Task persistence using localStorage.

